{
  "stem": "5551.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Each of her children has four children in turn, and there isn't one of them more delightful than the other.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Nothing but precious, all of them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She lost her husband later on cancer, and remarried, and lives now in-- in Toronto.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Very close to me, she has become much like a sister.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Her children, too.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We stayed with my uncle.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I already said, he always smiled.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nothing bothered him, and we were a family of four.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It wasn't that convenient for him, but it meant nothing to him, though.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "A wonderful host.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I have no idea about Tarnow.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I only know that the Germans killed all of them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Except for this one girl-- Ida is her name.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She survived and, strangely enough by coincidence, she just about was parallel with us in the camps that we sent-- we were sent to.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Tarnow we were until towards the end of 1939, when we went to Gorlice, where my grandparents and my mother's siblings lived.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we tried to reestablish ourselves.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But soon, the anti-Jewish laws came into effect.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were limited in-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in mobility, and we were locked, kind of, in-- in certain neighborhoods that were meant for Jews only.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was not quite a ghetto in the sense it wasn't closed, but it was something like it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a precursor of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were made to wear a Star of David, a yellow star.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I would quote Wiesel's description of it, 'our world was made to be smaller and smaller.' It started just then.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
